ss=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Progressively measurable process. A sequence of functions `u` is said to be progressively\nmeasurable with respect to a filtration `f` if at each point in time `i`, `u` restricted to\n`Set.Iic i × Ω` is measurable with respect to the product `MeasurableSpace` structure where the\nσ-algebra used for `Ω` is `f i`.\nThe usual definition uses the interval `[0,i]`, which we replace by `Set.Iic i`. We recover the\nusual definition for index types `ℝ≥0` or `ℕ`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Adapted.html#MeasureTheory.ProgMeasurable","kind":"def","line":178,"name":"MeasureTheory.ProgMeasurable","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Process/Adapted.lean#L178-L185"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Adapted.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration.stronglyAdapted_natural\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Filtration</span>.<span class=\"name\">stronglyAdapted_natural</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a h